definition: to put on a hat/to be first/to dub
COVID-19, the coronavirus disease identified in 2019
pinyin: er4 ling2 yi1 jiu3 guan1 zhuang4 bing4 du2 bing4

definition: novel coronavirus (esp. SARS-CoV-2, the virus causing COVID-19)
pinyin: xin1 xing2 guan1 zhuang4 bing4 du2

sentences.english: Infection with a novel coronavirus has been implicated as the cause of SARS.
sentences.chinese: 一種新的冠狀病毒已被確定爲本病的致病因子。

sentences.english: FIP is a disease that is related to Corona virus.
sentences.chinese: 國際製藥聯合會是一種疾病，這是相關的冠狀病毒。

sentences.english: As with canine Parvovirus, there is no specific treatment for canine Coronavirus.
sentences.chinese: 與犬細小病毒，但沒有具體的治療犬冠狀病毒。

sentences.english: The World Health Organization has confirmed a novel coronavirus to be the causative agent for SARS.
sentences.chinese: 世界衛生組織已證實病原是一種新發現的冠狀病毒。

sentences.english: Its name, the Middle East Respiratory System Coronavirus.
sentences.chinese: 它的名字是中東呼吸系統冠狀病毒。

sentences.english: Reports of a new strain of the coronavirus overseas is nowhere near the movie version of an outbreak.
sentences.chinese: 報道的海外新菌株冠狀病毒遠不及電影版的爆發。
